Afropop singer, Adekunle Temitope aka Small Doctor has advised Nigerian politicians to remain selfless and draw inspiration from the Nigerians whose legacies remain June 12. Small Doctor made this known when he joined youths who converged at Gani Fawehinmi Park, Ojota, Lagos, for a protest. The artist stopped to cheer and address the protesters. Speaking at the venue, Small Doctor said politicians should be selfless in their services and must continue to draw inspiration from June 12, its legacies, and martyrs. He further urged the protesters to never stop demanding their rights from the government but peacefully. “We have the right to protest, it is our right but should be a peaceful protest. Don’t let us allow hoodlums or thugs to hijack our peaceful protect,” he said.